   "source": [
    "# Project Neptune: Coastal Flood Prediction 🌊\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook is configured to run the Project Neptune pipeline directly on Kaggle. It leverages Kaggle's free GPU resources to accelerate the Graph Vision Transformer (FloodFormerGV).\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "# Locate project root depending on how you loaded the code in Kaggle\n",
    "# If loaded via GitHub sync or dataset, it might be in a subdirectory\n",
    "if os.path.exists('/kaggle/input/project-neptune'):\n",
    "    %cd /kaggle/input/project-neptune\n",
    "elif os.path.exists('/kaggle/working/Project-Neptune'):\n",
    "    %cd /kaggle/working/Project-Neptune\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    # Assume we are already in the correct directory\n",
    "    pass\n",
    "print(\"Working Directory:\", os.getcwd())\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🔑 Step 1: Configure API Keys\n",
    "1. Go to **Add-ons -> Secrets** in the top menu of your Kaggle notebook.\n",
    "2. Add `CDS_URL` with value `https://cds.climate.copernicus.eu/api`\n",
    "3. Add `CDS_KEY` with your token (e.g. `f1eef164-...`)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from kaggle_secrets import UserSecretsClient\n",
    "import os\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    user_secrets = UserSecretsClient()\n",
    "    cds_url = user_secrets.get_secret(\"CDS_URL\")\n",
    "    cds_key = user_secrets.get_secret(\"CDS_KEY\")\n",
    "    rc_path = os.path.expanduser('~/.cdsapirc')\n",
    "    with open(rc_path, 'w') as f:\n",
    "        f.write(f\"url: {cds_url}\\nkey: {cds_key}\\n\")\n",
    "    print(\"✅ Copernicus Data Store credentials successfully injected.\")\n",
    "except Exception as e:\n",
    "    print(\"⚠️ Warning: Could not find Kaggle Secrets for CDS.\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📦 Step 2: Install Dependencies\n",
    "We install requirements and dynamically fetch PyTorch Geometric bindings based on Kaggle's specific CUDA version.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "if os.path.exists(\"requirements.txt\"):\n",
    "    !pip install -r requirements.txt\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"requirements.txt not found, installing core packages manually...\")\n",
    "    !pip install cdsapi ecmwf-datastores-client xarray rasterio pyyaml\n",
    "\n",
    "!pip install torch_geometric\n",
    "\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "torch_version = torch.__version__.split(\"+\")[0]\n",
    "cuda_version = \"cu\" + torch.version.cuda.replace(\".\", \"\")\n",
    "url = f\"https://data.pyg.org/whl/torch-{torch_version}+{cuda_version}.html\"\n",
    "print(f\"Installing PyG extensions from: {url}\")\n",
    "!pip install pyg_lib torch_scatter torch_sparse torch_cluster torch_spline_conv -f {url}\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🚀 Step 3: Run the Pipeline\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!python flood_prediction/main.py\n"
   ]
  }
